MBOMBELA &#8211; On Sunday the winner of SA Idols Season 12 will be announced at Carnival City&#8217;s Big Top Arena in Brakpan. It is the first time in four years that a Lowvelder will not be in contention.The last two hopefuls to compete for the top spot, Thami Shobede and Noma Khumalo, both hail from KwaZulu-Natal. In 2014 Bongi Silinda from Mbombela was the first runner-up. Although Silinda didn&#8217;t win the competition, it has opened doors for her and she has released an album of her own.